&lt;P&gt;Page #20 in the QS manual states that an unstressed terminal -Y sound&lt;BR&gt;should be represented by letter #26 with letter #27 reserved for&lt;BR&gt;stressed terminal -Y sound.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;From a dry technical standpoint, in Junior Quikscript, it would be&lt;BR&gt;appropriate to spell &quot;busy&quot; as &quot;bizI&quot; since this suffix rule is on&lt;BR&gt;page #20 &amp; Junior Quikscript ends on page #12. However, in Senior&lt;BR&gt;Quikscript, &quot;bizi&quot; is appropriate. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;--- In &lt;A href=&quot;mailto:Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;Read_Alphabet@&lt;WBR&gt;yahoogroups.&lt;WBR&gt;com&lt;/A&gt;, &quot;pete_a90&quot; &lt;pete_a90@..&lt;WBR&gt;.&gt; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; I&#39;m confused about this letter because according to both the manual&lt;BR&gt;&gt; and&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;A href=&quot;http://home.earthlink.net/~sbartok1632/quik/qprojects/qdict/qdic_e/b.htm&quot;&gt;http://home.&lt;WBR&gt;earthlink.&lt;WBR&gt;net/~sbartok1632&lt;WBR&gt;/quik/qprojects/&lt;WBR&gt;qdict/qdic_&lt;WBR&gt;e/b.htm&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; busy = 
bizi&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I would have thought it would be pronounced&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; bizI instead (i.e. with letter #27 in place of the y).&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN style=&quot;COLOR: white&quot;&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;
